I kind of like this - as others said, it's relatable and has a certain charm - but I can't help but feel it's pretty bare. 'Hey isn't it funny when you go into the store and what you want isn't there' is a nice basis for a story but this is a very straightforward application of that. I don't think it necessarily needs deep and meaningful twists or extra fluff, but the test log was very much a 'what we said would happen in the description did, indeed, happen' sort of affair. Novote from me.







